  "name": "Triangle-and-two defense",
  "category": "Defense",
  "sub_category": "Zone",
  "description": "A sophisticated hybrid defense that combines the principles of man-to-man and zone. It initially aligns as a traditional zone (e.g., 2-3 or 1-2-2), but once offensive players enter a defender's designated area, it transforms into man-to-man principles. Defenders aggressively match up with attackers in their zone, pass off cutters to teammates via elite communication, and seamlessly switch to maintain pressure without leaving the paint vulnerable.",
